    Partial Info.plist merged into the macOS bundle by Tauri at packaging time.
    Hosts the user-facing permission strings shown by the system prompt the
    first time the app calls `getUserMedia` / `getDisplayMedia`. Without
    these keys macOS rejects the request silently with `NotAllowedError`,
    leaving the user alone in voice channels.
-->
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
    <key>NSMicrophoneUsageDescription</key>
    <string>Void needs microphone access so other members of your voice channels can hear you.</string>

    <key>NSCameraUsageDescription</key>
    <string>Void uses the camera for video calls inside voice channels.</string>

    <key>NSScreenCaptureUsageDescription</key>
    <string>Void can share your screen with other members of a voice channel.</string>
</dict>
</plist>

